6.01	Dodge_Sprinter	Mercedes-Benz Sprinter	The Mercedes-Benz Sprinter is a light and heavy commercial vehicle, built by Daimler AG of Stuttgart, Germany as a van, chassis cab and minibus, and sold as a Mercedes model, except in the U.S. where it is built from complete knock down (CKD) kits and was sold by Freightliner until 2010 when Mercedes-Benz of North America took over sales and service of the vehicles. Their automobile platform and bodyshell is also used in a joint venture with Volkswagen Commercial Vehicles who made the Volkswagen LT and the Volkswagen Crafter.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0d/Mercedes-Benz_Sprinter.JPG/250px-Mercedes-Benz_Sprinter.JPG
